  <Docs>
    <summary>Applies metadata to an assembly that indicates that a type is an unmanaged type. This class cannot be inherited.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[

## Remarks
 Compilers use the <xref:System.Runtime.CompilerServices.NativeCppClassAttribute> attribute when building assemblies to indicate that a type is an unmanaged type defined in C or C++. This attribute is used later to correctly handle the unmanaged type when it is imported during interop.

 ]]></format>
    </remarks>
  </Docs>
